From 3390050b9dcf07afbf13af41d8a680a95122d50d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Your Name <you@example.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 04:39:29 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] drm: add debugfs non_desktop_override for connectors

Add a per-connector debugfs file, non_desktop_override, that directly
forces the immutable non-desktop KMS property to a given value -
independent of EDID content entirely.

Motivation: userspace has one existing lever for this today,
edid_override, which works by making drm_do_get_edid() return
fabricated EDID bytes instead of reading real hardware, for every
subsequent probe. That's the right tool for testing EDID parsing
itself, but the wrong tool for this: forcing non-desktop on a real,
physically-present headset means either patching the device's real
EDID in place (leaving its actual, possibly link-bandwidth-dependent
mode list intact, but coupling this to the pre-existing timing/mode
concerns any EDID edit carries) or replacing it wholesale (losing the
real mode list, and along with it the kernel's own useful pruning of
modes the link can't actually carry). In both cases, EDID is being
used as the only available lever for a property that has nothing to
do with EDID content on hardware where the real information ("this
is a headset, don't treat it like a desktop monitor") isn't otherwise
being communicated to the kernel at all - no DisplayID 2.0 Display
Product Type block, not in the hardcoded edid_quirk_list[] table, no
Microsoft VSDB. non-desktop is already computed and stored independent
of any of these three specific sources; this adds a fourth.

non_desktop is DRM_MODE_PROP_IMMUTABLE, meaning userspace cannot set it
through the normal object-property ioctl path, but kernel-side code is
explicitly permitted to update its stored value directly via
drm_object_property_set_value() - the same mechanism already used for
vrr_capable, passive_vrr_capable, and allm_capable, none of which need
an EDID round-trip either. This applies that same established pattern
to non-desktop.

drm_connector_non_desktop_override_set() does three things: updates
connector->display_info.non_desktop directly, pushes that value into
the KMS property via drm_object_property_set_value(), and calls
drm_sysfs_connector_property_event() - not
drm_sysfs_connector_hotplug_event() - to notify userspace. The latter
goes through a full reprobe (drm_helper_hpd_irq_event() and friends),
which re-reads the EDID and regenerates the mode list; the property
event does not. Worth being precise about what this does and doesn't
avoid: drm_sysfs_connector_property_event() still sets HOTPLUG=1 in the
emitted uevent (that env var name is reused for property-change events
too, not something this patch controls), so a compositor watching for
hotplug-shaped uevents does still see one. What's actually skipped is
the kernel-side DDC read and mode-list regeneration a real reprobe
would otherwise do.

update_display_info() consults the override once, at the very end,
after every EDID-derived source (quirk table, Microsoft VSDB,
DisplayID) has already been evaluated via drm_edid_has_internal_quirk()
- so a real subsequent probe (hotplug, or a forced reprobe via the
connector's existing status file) recomputes non_desktop from the EDID
as normal and then has the active override applied on top, rather than
the override being silently lost on the next hotplug.

drm_connector_non_desktop_override_reset() intentionally does not try
to synchronously resolve display_info.non_desktop or the KMS property
back to an EDID-derived value - matches drm_edid_override_reset()'s own
existing precedent exactly: it also only clears the override and
relies on the next real probe to naturally pick up the change.

Deliberately debugfs, not sysfs: the precedent set by the existing
force/edid_override debugfs files (and 2014's dri-devel discussion
around exposing 'force' via sysfs, where the response was 'please make
it a debugfs feature... we shouldn't expose interfaces in sysfs that
aren't part of the core API') suggests connector-behavior override
knobs like this belong there first. Promotion to a real, committed
sysfs ABI is a reasonable follow-up once this has seen real use.

Verified against the actual target kernel version (7.1.3), not just a
close approximation: fetched real source from kernel.org, configured
with CONFIG_DRM=y, and compiled drm_edid.o, drm_connector.o, and
drm_debugfs.o (the three files with real content changes) individually
- zero errors, zero warnings. Also verified the patch applies cleanly
(git apply --check) to a freshly reset, untouched checkout of the same
source, not just the working copy it was developed against.

An earlier version of this patch was developed and verified against
Ubuntu's 6.8.0 kernel source instead, which turned out to be different
enough from 7.1.3 for real patch-context drift in three spots (all in
drivers/gpu/drm/drm_connector.c, drm_crtc_internal.h, and drm_edid.c) -
none were logic changes, just intervening lines added nearby upstream
between versions (new hdmi/cec mutex_init() calls, a new
drm_edid_find_extension() declaration, and the EDID_QUIRK_NON_DESKTOP
check moving from direct bitmask access to a drm_edid_has_internal_quirk()
helper call) - but real enough that the 6.8.0-verified patch failed to
apply here at all. This version is rebuilt and reverified against 7.1.3
specifically rather than assumed compatible.
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/drm_connector.c     |   2 +
 drivers/gpu/drm/drm_crtc_internal.h |   3 +
 drivers/gpu/drm/drm_debugfs.c       |  53 ++++++++++++++
 drivers/gpu/drm/drm_edid.c          | 110 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 include/drm/drm_connector.h         |  21 ++++++
 5 files changed, 189 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_connector.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_connector.c
index 47dc53c..e95e3c6 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_connector.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_connector.c
@@ -283,6 +283,8 @@ static int drm_connector_init_only(struct drm_device *dev,
 	mutex_init(&connector->cec.mutex);
 	mutex_init(&connector->eld_mutex);
 	mutex_init(&connector->edid_override_mutex);
+	mutex_init(&connector->non_desktop_override_mutex);
+	connector->non_desktop_override_set = false;
 	mutex_init(&connector->hdmi.infoframes.lock);
 	mutex_init(&connector->hdmi_audio.lock);
 	connector->edid_blob_ptr = NULL;
diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_crtc_internal.h b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_crtc_internal.h
index c094092..6046715 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_crtc_internal.h
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_crtc_internal.h
@@ -298,6 +298,9 @@ void drm_mode_fixup_1366x768(struct drm_display_mode *mode);
 int drm_edid_override_show(struct drm_connector *connector, struct seq_file *m);
 int drm_edid_override_set(struct drm_connector *connector, const void *edid, size_t size);
 int drm_edid_override_reset(struct drm_connector *connector);
+int drm_connector_non_desktop_override_show(struct drm_connector *connector, struct seq_file *m);
+int drm_connector_non_desktop_override_set(struct drm_connector *connector, bool value);
+int drm_connector_non_desktop_override_reset(struct drm_connector *connector);
 const u8 *drm_edid_find_extension(const struct drm_edid *drm_edid,
 				  int ext_id, int *ext_index);
 void drm_edid_cta_sad_get(const struct cea_sad *cta_sad, u8 *sad);
diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_debugfs.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_debugfs.c
index ae1c612..54ab264 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_debugfs.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_debugfs.c
@@ -623,6 +623,55 @@ static const struct file_operations drm_edid_fops = {
 	.write = edid_write
 };
 
+static int non_desktop_override_show(struct seq_file *m, void *data)
+{
+	return drm_connector_non_desktop_override_show(m->private, m);
+}
+
+static int non_desktop_override_open(struct inode *inode, struct file *file)
+{
+	struct drm_connector *dev = inode->i_private;
+
+	return single_open(file, non_desktop_override_show, dev);
+}
+
+static ssize_t non_desktop_override_write(struct file *file, const char __user *ubuf,
+					  size_t len, loff_t *offp)
+{
+	struct seq_file *m = file->private_data;
+	struct drm_connector *connector = m->private;
+	char buf[8];
+	int ret;
+
+	if (len > sizeof(buf) - 1)
+		return -EINVAL;
+
+	if (copy_from_user(buf, ubuf, len))
+		return -EFAULT;
+
+	buf[len] = '\0';
+
+	if (sysfs_streq(buf, "reset"))
+		ret = drm_connector_non_desktop_override_reset(connector);
+	else if (sysfs_streq(buf, "0"))
+		ret = drm_connector_non_desktop_override_set(connector, false);
+	else if (sysfs_streq(buf, "1"))
+		ret = drm_connector_non_desktop_override_set(connector, true);
+	else
+		return -EINVAL;
+
+	return ret ? ret : len;
+}
+
+static const struct file_operations drm_non_desktop_override_fops = {
+	.owner = THIS_MODULE,
+	.open = non_desktop_override_open,
+	.read = seq_read,
+	.llseek = seq_lseek,
+	.release = single_release,
+	.write = non_desktop_override_write
+};
+
 
 static const struct file_operations drm_connector_fops = {
 	.owner = THIS_MODULE,
@@ -807,6 +856,10 @@ void drm_debugfs_connector_add(struct drm_connector *connector)
 	debugfs_create_file("edid_override", 0644, root, connector,
 			    &drm_edid_fops);
 
+	/* non-desktop override */
+	debugfs_create_file("non_desktop_override", 0644, root, connector,
+			    &drm_non_desktop_override_fops);
+
 	/* vrr range */
 	debugfs_create_file("vrr_range", 0444, root, connector,
 			    &vrr_range_fops);
diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_edid.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_edid.c
index 404208b..66d30cb 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_edid.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_edid.c
@@ -45,6 +45,7 @@
 #include <drm/drm_edid.h>
 #include <drm/drm_eld.h>
 #include <drm/drm_encoder.h>
+#include <drm/drm_sysfs.h>
 #include <drm/drm_print.h>
 
 #include "drm_crtc_internal.h"
@@ -2319,6 +2320,100 @@ int drm_edid_override_reset(struct drm_connector *connector)
 	return 0;
 }
 
+/*
+ * For debugfs non_desktop_override implementation.
+ *
+ * Unlike edid_override, this does not wait for (or require) a probe to take
+ * effect: it updates the connector's non-desktop display_info field and the
+ * corresponding immutable KMS property directly, right here, and returns
+ * only a lightweight property-change notification rather than a full
+ * hotplug - see drm_connector_non_desktop_override_set()'s own comment for
+ * why. A real probe (hotplug or forced) still recomputes non_desktop from
+ * the EDID as normal; update_display_info() consults the override *after*
+ * that computation so a subsequent real probe doesn't silently undo it.
+ */
+int drm_connector_non_desktop_override_show(struct drm_connector *connector, struct seq_file *m)
+{
+	mutex_lock(&connector->non_desktop_override_mutex);
+
+	if (connector->non_desktop_override_set)
+		seq_printf(m, "%d\n", connector->non_desktop_override_value);
+	else
+		seq_puts(m, "unset\n");
+
+	mutex_unlock(&connector->non_desktop_override_mutex);
+
+	return 0;
+}
+
+int drm_connector_non_desktop_override_set(struct drm_connector *connector, bool value)
+{
+	struct drm_device *dev = connector->dev;
+	int ret;
+
+	drm_dbg_kms(dev, "[CONNECTOR:%d:%s] non-desktop override set to %d\n",
+		    connector->base.id, connector->name, value);
+
+	mutex_lock(&connector->non_desktop_override_mutex);
+	connector->non_desktop_override_set = true;
+	connector->non_desktop_override_value = value;
+	mutex_unlock(&connector->non_desktop_override_mutex);
+
+	connector->display_info.non_desktop = value;
+
+	ret = drm_object_property_set_value(&connector->base,
+					    dev->mode_config.non_desktop_property,
+					    value);
+	if (ret) {
+		drm_dbg_kms(dev, "[CONNECTOR:%d:%s] non-desktop property update failed (%d)\n",
+			    connector->base.id, connector->name, ret);
+		return ret;
+	}
+
+	/*
+	 * Deliberately not drm_sysfs_connector_hotplug_event(): that path
+	 * goes through a full reprobe (drm_helper_hpd_irq_event() and
+	 * friends), which re-reads the EDID and regenerates the mode list -
+	 * exactly the DDC round-trip and mode churn this override exists to
+	 * avoid needing. drm_sysfs_connector_property_event() still sets
+	 * HOTPLUG=1 in the emitted uevent (that field name is reused for
+	 * property-change events too, not something this function controls),
+	 * so a compositor watching for hotplug-shaped uevents does still see
+	 * one - what's actually skipped is the kernel-side EDID read and
+	 * mode-list regeneration a real reprobe would otherwise do.
+	 */
+	drm_sysfs_connector_property_event(connector, dev->mode_config.non_desktop_property);
+
+	return 0;
+}
+
+int drm_connector_non_desktop_override_reset(struct drm_connector *connector)
+{
+	drm_dbg_kms(connector->dev, "[CONNECTOR:%d:%s] non-desktop override reset\n",
+		    connector->base.id, connector->name);
+
+	mutex_lock(&connector->non_desktop_override_mutex);
+	connector->non_desktop_override_set = false;
+	mutex_unlock(&connector->non_desktop_override_mutex);
+
+	/*
+	 * Deliberately not resolving connector->display_info.non_desktop or
+	 * the KMS property back to an EDID-derived value synchronously here
+	 * - doing that correctly needs either a fresh DDC read or a cached
+	 * drm_edid to recompute from, and there's no cheap, safe way to get
+	 * either from this context without either re-probing (which reset
+	 * has no more right to force than any other debugfs override does -
+	 * edid_override_reset() itself doesn't) or inventing new caching
+	 * this connector doesn't otherwise need. This matches
+	 * drm_edid_override_reset()'s own precedent exactly: it also only
+	 * clears the override and relies on the next real probe (hotplug,
+	 * or a userspace-forced one via the connector's `status` file) to
+	 * naturally pick the change up.
+	 */
+
+	return 0;
+}
+
 /**
  * drm_edid_override_connector_update - add modes from override/firmware EDID
  * @connector: connector we're probing
@@ -6838,6 +6933,21 @@ static void update_display_info(struct drm_connector *connector,
 		info->non_desktop = true;
 	}
 
+	/*
+	 * A debugfs non_desktop_override, if active, takes precedence over
+	 * whatever the EDID itself says - applied last, after every other
+	 * EDID-derived source (quirk table, Microsoft VSDB, DisplayID) has
+	 * already had its say, so it genuinely overrides rather than merely
+	 * racing them. This is what lets an override set once survive a
+	 * real subsequent probe (hotplug, forced reprobe) undisturbed: this
+	 * function runs again on every such probe, and this check runs
+	 * every time it does.
+	 */
+	mutex_lock(&connector->non_desktop_override_mutex);
+	if (connector->non_desktop_override_set)
+		info->non_desktop = connector->non_desktop_override_value;
+	mutex_unlock(&connector->non_desktop_override_mutex);
+
 	if (drm_edid_has_internal_quirk(connector, EDID_QUIRK_CAP_DSC_15BPP))
 		info->max_dsc_bpp = 15;
 
diff --git a/include/drm/drm_connector.h b/include/drm/drm_connector.h
index f83f28c..1efac3f 100644
--- a/include/drm/drm_connector.h
+++ b/include/drm/drm_connector.h
@@ -2264,6 +2264,27 @@ struct drm_connector {
 	 */
 	struct mutex edid_override_mutex;
 
+	/**
+	 * @non_desktop_override_set: Whether a non-desktop override is
+	 * active, set via debugfs.
+	 *
+	 * Do not modify or access outside of the
+	 * drm_connector_non_desktop_override_* family of functions.
+	 */
+	bool non_desktop_override_set;
+
+	/**
+	 * @non_desktop_override_value: The forced non-desktop value when
+	 * @non_desktop_override_set is true. Meaningless otherwise.
+	 */
+	bool non_desktop_override_value;
+
+	/**
+	 * @non_desktop_override_mutex: Protect access to
+	 * non_desktop_override_set and non_desktop_override_value.
+	 */
+	struct mutex non_desktop_override_mutex;
+
 	/** @epoch_counter: used to detect any other changes in connector, besides status */
 	u64 epoch_counter;
 
-- 
2.43.0

